---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet"
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Hi, I'm Jack. I'm a software engineer deeply passionate about <strong>systems engineering, virtualization, and networking</strong>. I spend most of my time exploring the boundaries between the Linux kernel and user space, or building high-performance networking tools.
	</p>

	<p>
		My core strengths involve bridging the gap between low-level system APIs and modern developer experiences. I enjoy taking complex, "scary" infrastructure concepts (like TAP devices, KVM hypervisors, and iptables NAT routing) and wrapping them in elegant, accessible APIs.
	</p>

	<h3>Technical Strengths</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Systems Programming:</strong> Proficient in <strong>Rust</strong>. I build fast, concurrent, and memory-safe systems applications, often leveraging <code>tokio</code> for async I/O multiplexing.</li>
		<li><strong>Virtualization (KVM/Firecracker):</strong> Hands-on experience building custom microVM orchestrators. I've designed systems that boot ephemeral, fully-isolated Linux sandboxes in milliseconds.</li>
		<li><strong>Linux Networking:</strong> Extensive knowledge of the Linux network stack. I routinely work with virtual interfaces (TAP/TUN), routing tables, NAT configurations via iptables, and socket programming.</li>
		<li><strong>Inter-process Communication (IPC):</strong> Deep dive experience with Unix Domain Sockets and VSOCK for host-to-guest communication bridges.</li>
		<li><strong>Web Architecture:</strong> Bridging the low-level systems with the web, using WebSockets to tunnel binary protocols (like terminal serial output) directly to browser frontends.</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Currently, I'm hacking on <code>firecracker-rust</code>, an experimental orchestrator designed to provide instant, disposable, browser-based sandboxes without the heavy overhead of Docker or Kubernetes.
	</p>

	<p>
		When I'm not wrestling with <code>Resource Busy</code> networking errors or kernel panics, I'm probably writing about what I've learned here on this blog.
	</p>
</Layout>
